# MerchantPro Integration

## Backend
- Credentials from `.env`: `MERCHANTPRO_API_URL`, `MERCHANTPRO_API_USERNAME`, `MERCHANTPRO_API_PASSWORD`
- Environment selector from `.env`: `ENVIRONMENT` (`dev|qa|prod`) for config files like `product_statuses_<ENVIRONMENT>.json` with fallback to default files
- Basic Auth for MerchantPro API calls
- Service layer: `backend/app/services/merchantpro.py`, `backend/app/services/orders.py`
- App-level rate limit guard: ~3 calls/sec and 90 calls/min in service layer; still handle MerchantPro `429` gracefully
- Retry: 3 retries with exponential backoff on 5xx
- Timeout: 30 seconds

## Orders Endpoint
- MerchantPro: `GET /api/v2/orders` (see https://docs.merchantpro.com/api/endpoints/orders)
- Pagination: `start` offset (default 0) + `limit` (app defaults to 100, max 100)
- Response: `{ data: [...], meta: { count, links } }`
- Thin proxy route `GET /api/merchantpro/orders` uses query param `order_status` and maps it to MerchantPro `status`

## Data Model
- Orders have `line_items[]` with `meta_fields.dobavljac`, `meta_fields.komercijalista`
- Line items have `status` with `id`, `name`, `color`
- Denormalize for table: one row per line item, order data repeated

## Error Handling
- 401/403 → redirect to login or show auth error
- 500/504 → show "Service unavailable" or "Request timed out" in modal
